content:
Provide Web Forms with Web-to-Case

Use Web-to-Case to automatically turn support inquiries into cases. Set up a web form on your website and decide which case fields to include.

Required editions: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience, Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

Setting up a web form:

* Set case submission preferences in Setup
* Choose case fields to include (e.g., Contact Name, Phone, or custom field)
* Use the handy tool to generate HTML code for the form
* Add the HTML to your website

When a customer submits the form, they receive an automatic email and a case is created. The case can be automatically linked to the relevant contact and account based on the customer's email address.

Web-to-Case guidelines and limits:

* Generates up to 5,000 cases per day (more if higher limit requested)
* Supports adding reCAPTCHA v2 to filter out spam cases
* Does not support attachments or rich text fields

Before setting up your web form with Web-to-Case, complete these steps:

* Turn On and Customize Web-to-Case
* Gather customer support requests directly from your website
* Add the form to your website
* Generate and test your Web-to-Case form
* Prevent spam cases with reCAPTCHA
* Review guidelines and limits for Web-to-Case
title: Setting Up Web-to-Case in Service Cloud
